

---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout title="paradox">
  <Article
    title="paradox"
    section="self"
    updated="archive draft"
  >
    <p>
      paradox is the coexistence of opposing truths. it appears when two ideas
      or experiences contradict each other, yet both remain valid.
    </p>

    <p>
      instead of resolving tension, paradox holds it. the self is often shaped
      not by choosing one side, but by remaining within the contradiction.
    </p>

    <p>
      because of this, paradox can feel unstable—but it also opens a deeper
      level of understanding.
    </p>

    <h2>tension</h2>

    <p>
      paradox creates tension between opposites: control and freedom, certainty
      and doubt, stability and change.
    </p>

    <p>
      this tension is not a flaw. it is part of how complexity is held.
    </p>

    <h2>integration</h2>

    <p>
      instead of eliminating one side, paradox asks for integration. both
      elements are included, even if they do not fully align.
    </p>

    <p>
      this expands the range of what the self can contain.
    </p>

    <h2>movement</h2>

    <p>
      paradox often leads to movement. when a stable answer is not possible,
      the self continues searching, adapting, and shifting.
    </p>

    <p>
      this movement connects directly to the wanderer.
    </p>

    <div class="mini-links">
      <a class="link-blue" href="/self">back to self index</a>
      <a class="link-blue" href="/self/wanderer">continue to: wanderer</a>
      <a class="link-red" href="/self/play">play</a>
    </div>
  </Article>
</Layout>